This paper proposes an automatic design framework for swarm pattern formation, which involves the optimization of a gene regulatory network (GRN) model using multi-objective genetic programming. The paper focuses on the application of this framework to swarm robotics, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of genetic programming and optimization algorithms also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the robustness of the evolved models, which could be relevant to the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
